Forwarding anonymous report from #Mapy.cz user, please verify: 'This trail is in bad condition and very dangerous. The trail is bad at the whole from Malenshchek waterfall to Selce, but the worst part is right near Selce. It is not solid, it's loose and cannot hold the weight of a person. And the fall is high and can only be lethal. If you start from Selce, then you see it immediately and return safely. But if you start from Vrsno, this is the last point before Selce and you might not want to return back. In order to keep people from danger I'd suggest to delete the trail from Brinta wtf to Selce, so that those who start from Vrsna will plan to return back more safe way rather than risk going that trail to Selce.'

I think all OSM should do is strive to provide accurate data (which seems to be the case here). It is up to the user to decide what to do of that.  For alpine enthusiasts, this well tagged path might be very valuable and exactly what they're looking for, so I'd refrain from deleting it.
